Documentation

Changelog

LTS release 1.XPubliée le 2024-07-01

SDK.Medias for C#

[1.8.0] - 2026-01-16

Changed

  • Update code to remove compilation warnings

[1.7.0] - 2025-11-20

Fixed

  • MediaEncoder object

    • CreateMediaVideoEncoder() method: No more use GlobalQuality but GopSize to manage key frame

  • MediaInput, MediaRtpInput, MediaFiltered objects

    • exception could occurred when end of input file is reached

Added

  • Added .Net 10.0 as target framework

Changed

  • MediaInput, MediaRtpInput, MediaFiltered objects
    • standardizes RaiseOnVideoSample() methods

[1.6.0] - 2025-09-01

Fixed

  • MediaFilterd, MediaInput, MediaRtpInput objects:

    • Add more check when frame is converted / encoded
    • Use global lock to avoid crash when objects are released

  • MediaRtpInput object:

    • ensure to read all frames from packet

[1.5.0] - 2025-07-07

Added

  • MediaRtpInput object:
    • Add new optional parameters in constructor to allow to set ffmpeg options
    • Default options are now:
      • "reorder_queue_size" set to 32 (from 2048)
      • add "fflags" and set it to "+discardcorrupt+genpts+nofillin+nobuffer"

Changed

  • Update Microsoft.Extensions.Logging.Abstractions dependency package to v9.0.0 (from v8.0.0)

[1.4.0] - 2025-04-23

Fixed

  • Noisy sound when using Microphone as audio input stream

Changed

  • MediaInput service: in FromScreenDevice() and FromWebcamDevice() methods add loggerPrefix as optional parameter
  • Update Concentus dependency package to v2.2.2 (from v1.1.6)

[1.3.0] - 2025-03-12

Fixed

  • Devices service: when plugged/unplugged, store new devices list (screens, webcams, audio inputs and/or audio outputs) before to trigger device added / removed events. So it's possible to know this list when the event is received
  • MediaInput service: change how 'live stream' are managed
  • MediaRtpInput service: fix noisy incoming sound

Added

  • MediaInput service: FromScreenDevice(), FromWebcamDevice() methods
  • Helper: InitExternalLibraries() method now allows to initialize video features of SDL2 library
  • SDL2Helper: GetPixelFormat() to get SDL2 pixel format from ffmpeg pixel format
  • SDL2AudioOutput: ClearQueue()
  • SDL2 namespace: it's know totally public. Allow to access to all SDL2 features

[1.2.0] - 2024-11-22

Added

  • Devices service: OnWebcamDeviceAdded, OnWebcamDeviceRemoved, OnScreenDeviceAdded, OnScreenDeviceRemoved, OnAudioInputDeviceRemoved, OnAudioInputDeviceAdded, OnAudioOutputDeviceRemoved, OnAudioOutputDeviceAdded events
  • IMedia interface: Device property

Changed

  • Breaking IMedia interface: rename Stop() to StopAsync(), Pause() to PauseAsync(), SetVideoBitRate() to SetMaxVideoBitRate()
  • Breaking IMedia interface: remove Context() property
  • Breaking SDL2AudioInput object: needs now a Device in the constructor
  • Breaking SDL2AudioOutput object: needs now a Device in the constructor

[1.1.0] - 2024-10-01

Fixed

  • Improve the way to get/calculate Fps. (avoid NaN results)

Changed

  • IMediaVideoBase interface: add VideoStreamPixelFormat, VideoStreamTimeBase and VideoStreamSampleAspectRatio properties. MediaFiltered, MediaInput and MediaRtpInput are updated in consequence.
  • MediaFiltered object: add a constructor allowing to use IMediaVideo and/or IMediaAudio
  • MediaFiltered object: add AddMediaVideoInput() and AddMediaAudioInput()

[1.0.0] - 2024-07-01

Fixed

  • Improve the way to get/calculate Fps.
  • Avoid to use several streams when grabbing remote videos (for CCTV for example)

Changed

  • Use FFmpeg.AutoGen package v7.0.0 (from v6.0.0.2)
  • Use FFmpeg v7.0.1 shared libraries (from v6.0)
  • .Net 6.0 as target plateform has been removed (obsolete). .Net Std 2.0, 2.1 and .Net 8.0 are still in targets platform.

[0.0.9-STS] - 2024-03-19

Fixed

  • Allow to stream as video a JPG file (already possible with BMP, TIFF, PNG, WEBP (with one image), ...). GIF are also supported but not WEBP with animation due to FFmpeg limitation

Changed

  • Use Microsoft.Extensions.Logging.Abstractions v8.0.0.0 (from v7.0.0.0)

[0.0.8-STS] - 2024-01-15

Added

  • Add .Net 8.0 as target plateform (.Net Std 2.0, 2.1 and .Net 6.0 are still in targets platform) .Net 6.0 target platform will be removed in April.

[0.0.7-STS] - 2023-10-18

Added

  • MediaInput: allow to set widht, height, fps and bit rate used in encoding process. Take into account options set in the device
  • InputStreamDevice: Allow to set options

[0.0.6-STS] - 2023-09-05

Added

  • Add SetVideoBitRate() in MediaInput, MediaRtpInput and MediaFiltered

Changed

  • Use FFmpeg.AutoGen v6.0.0.2.
  • Use FFmpeg v6.0 libraries.
  • Enhancement in parser used to set filters

[0.0.5] - STS - 2023-07-07

  • .Net Core App 3.1 is no more targetted (already deprecated by Microsoft).
  • .Net Standardd 2.0 / 2.1 and .Net 6.0 are still targetted

[0.0.4] - STS - 2023-05-26

Fix

  • MediaRTPInput: Some internal values was not resetted correctly

  • MediaFiltered: When a new filter is set, it's necessary to dispose ALL previous objects to ensure to build correct frames

[0.0.3] - STS - 2023-02-10

Enhancements

It's now possible to decode RTP packets (Audio and/or Video) using MediaRtpInput object.

A valid SDP must be provided which describes codecs to use to decode them. It possible for the moment to manage only one Audio track and/or one Video Track.

If you have several tracks for a same media, it's possible to specify which one to use using an index.

[0.0.2] - STS - 2023-01-20

Enhancements

  • Major rework to avoid memory leak. Use of IDisposable interface in objects using unmanaged objects to ensure to dispose them.

  • Rework interfaces (IMedia, IMediaVideo, IMediaAudio, IMediaVideoOutput, IMediaAudioOutput) and inheritances in major objects: MediaInput, MediaFiltered and MediaOutput

API In details

  • IMedia interface (now inherits from IDisposable)

    • Loop: added To know if we loop automatically if the end of file is reached

    • Duration: added Duration in seconds of the Media (if not a life stream)

    • LiveStream: added To know the Media is a 'live steam' i.e. a remote stream for a live stream server, live camera or an IPTV for example

    • OnEndOfFile: added Event raised when the Media as reached the end of the file.

    • Init: added To init the media.

  • IMediaVideo interface:

    • Loop: removed

    • Duration: removed

    • LiveStream: removed

    • Init: removed

  • IMediaVideoOutput interface: added

    • GotVideoFrame: added To add Video Frame to this Media Video Output

  • MediaFiltered now inherits from IMediaVideo and IMediaAudio

  • SDL2AudioInput implements IMedia interface

  • SDL2AudioOutput implements IMedia interface

  • MediaFormat static class: remoced data/methods are now in Helper class

[0.0.1] - STS - 2022-12-07

This is the first version of this SDK.

Please refer to the "getting started" guides for feature details
